'''Sean Bean''' (born 17 April 1959) is an English actor who has worked in film, television and theatrical productions, as well as providing voice-overs for commercials and computer games.

He first became well known for his portrayal of [[wikipedia:Richard Sharpe (fictional character)|Richard Sharpe]] in the long-running British television series [[wikipedia:Sharpe (TV series)|''Sharpe'']], before appearing as [[wikipedia:Boromir|Boromir]] in [[wikipedia:Peter Jackson|Peter Jackson]]'s [[wikipedia:Lord of the Rings film trilogy|''Lord of the Rings'']] movie trilogy. He has also carved out a role as a [[wikipedia:Hollywood|Hollywood]] villain, appearing in antagonistic roles in films such as [[wikipedia:Patriot Games (film)|''Patriot Games'']], [[wikipedia:GoldenEye|''GoldenEye'']] and [[wikipedia:National Treasure (film)|''National Treasure'']].Other notable works include [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alec_Trevelyan &lt;u&gt;Alec Trevelyan&lt;/u&gt;] in the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Bond_(film_series) &lt;u&gt;James Bond film&lt;/u&gt;] ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoldenEye &lt;u&gt;GoldenEye&lt;/u&gt;]'', [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odysseus &lt;u&gt;Odysseus&lt;/u&gt;] in ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troy_(film) &lt;u&gt;Troy&lt;/u&gt;]'', Dr. Merrick in ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Island_(2005_film) &lt;u&gt;The Island&lt;/u&gt;]'', Ian Howe in ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Treasure_(film) &lt;u&gt;National Treasure&lt;/u&gt;]'', [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeus &lt;u&gt;Zeus&lt;/u&gt;] in ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percy_Jackson_%26_the_Olympians:_The_Lightning_Thief &lt;u&gt;Percy Jackson &amp; the Olympians: The Lightning Thief&lt;/u&gt;]'' and Ulric in ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Death_(film) &lt;u&gt;Black Death&lt;/u&gt;]''; which also starred ''Game of Thrones'' cast members [[Emun Elliott]] and [[Carice van Houten]].

He starred in [[HBO]]'s ''[[Game of Thrones (TV series)|Game of Thrones]]'' as Lord [[Eddard Stark]]. He was announced in the role on 19 July 2009. He appeared in nine episodes of the [[Season 1|first season]] (though was credited for all ten) before being written out, following the character's fate as depicted in the novel.

In an interview after [[Season 4]] aired, Bean mentioned that he would enjoy possibly returning to ''Game of Thrones'' to play Ned Stark in flashback scenes.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[http://winteriscoming.net/2014/07/18/sean-bean-wants-return-game-thrones/ Sean Bean wants to return to Game of Thrones]&lt;/ref&gt;
